|cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Hi Everyone and a very warm welcome (especially to all of the new faces) to the start of another series of sessions on the Precision Club bidding system. 

The course lasts about a year and all the sessions take place on Saturday evenings at 9pm GMT/UTC (which is normally 4pm EST until Daylight Savings kick in and then 5pm EDT till the end of October). 

Firstly for those of you who do not know me something by way of a quick introduction: I'm a 59 year old retired Police Sergeant now living in Scotland, but I spent most of my adult life in Manchester, England.

I've been playing Bridge since I was about 5 when my father taught me in to make up a four with him and my elder siblings. I became an instant fanatic. 

In the late 1970's and early 80's I ran a Bridge Club in Manchester (Bury Athenaeum) and taught beginner and Intermediate classes there.

I got sucked into Precision Club quite early after its introduction and have been a keen exponent of the system ever since. 

The system I will be teaching you is a Super-Precision system I developed initially with Bob Bradbury in about 1980, but in the mid 1980's I teamed up with Jason Hackett.  

He was then an England Junior and is now a full GB International and one of the UK's highest-ranked players in the WBF rankings.  

Together we developed the system a lot further and enjoyed a lot of success as a partnership and as a team with Paul Hackett and Justin Hackett. 


